A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.

What will your typical day look like?

As a Senior Consultant in our Data & AI team, focussing on Analytics & AI strategy, you will use your consulting skills to help clients make the right choices and take the right actions towards better use of Analytics and AI to achieve their business goals. As technical, strategy and industry experts, we understand clients’ challenges and define compelling strategies to meet their vision for becoming insight driven. A Senior Consultant will develop compelling interactions and presentations to showcases strategies, operating models and transformational business cases to clients across a range of industries, including Financial Services, Insurance, Government, Energy & Resources, Life Sciences & Healthcare, Telecommunications and Consumer Products.

Provide advisory services to business leaders and align AI, analytics, automation or data solutions to clients’ needs and develop an objectives, strategies and approaches that help clients transform
Build solid foundations of a business case and key recommendations for implementing analytical solutions for the client in alignment with their business agenda and strategic drivers
Analyse and evaluate current systems and structures of organisations where required, advising on business restructures, appropriate methods for collecting and analysing data and developing informed recommendations that shape or support the client’s business strategy
Comprehend and learn about client’s current business state, competitors’ point(s) of differentiation, industry landscape to support the identification, evaluation and selection of solutions that most effectively support clients’ strategic and business objectives
Conduct gap analysis on client’s current business landscape (i.e. operating model, business processes) to identify and define key recommendations and opportunities to uplift business performance
Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment
Ability to structure, break down and solve complex problems through synthesis of information, quantitative thinking and analysis
Ability to interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially foucssed recommendations to inform business decisions
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, capable of working effectively with people at all levels in an organization
Strong sense of ownership of outcomes with the drive to self-start and take initiative
A passion for working collaboratively with diverse teams, and to create an including environment for everyone
Ability to structure and facilitate client stakeholder interviews

The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. Technology has revolutionised the business space and is now more powerful than ever. But with great power comes great responsibility. That’s why we’re here. Part risk, part tech, we help clients protect their intellectual property and data!

Who are we?
Call us biased, but we’re probably the people with the coolest jobs at Deloitte. We help clients navigate tech risks through internal investigations and forensically analysing electronic evidence collected from phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems. Then, we design solutions that help our clients risk-align and future-proof their systems. Pretty cool, right?

What will your typical day look like?
We’ll be honest, it’s hard to tell you what an average day will look like at Deloitte because every day is just so different! Working on projects with an impressive portfolio of top-tier clients, you’ll get enviable experience as you:

Get exposure to tracing data breaches, intellectual property theft, misuse of computer systems and fraudulent activity (such as corruption and money laundering)
Roll up your sleeves to investigate electronic evidence collected from mobile phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems
Design solutions for engagements relating to electronic discovery, forensic investigations, legal support and digital forensics
Explore and identify patterns in data to underpin decisions and outcomes for clients
Track evidence and prepare detailed reports on forensic analysis findings

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.
We know that as a student, you may not necessarily have a ton of work experience, and that’s okay! At Deloitte, we value your potential to grow more than anything else.


Is studying a degree in Computer Science, IT, Software Engineering, Digital Forensics, Data Science or InfoSys
Is comfortable with turning ambiguous problems and open-ended tasks into creative solutions
Is passionate about investigating data to uncover hidden insights
Has a keen eye for detail and possesses strong communication and writing skills
Works best collaboratively – you thrive when working in a team!
Demonstrates a high level of integrity and maintains confidentiality at all times (this is integral considering the nature of work we do!)

Why Deloitte?
At Deloitte, we create positively differentiated work experiences that enable our people to feel valued and achieve their full potential. Deloitte Australia opens the door to a career that can cross borders virtually and physically across Asia Pacific to gain experience and access projects beyond Australia’s borders. We value difference, and embrace people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. Knowing that people work best in a variety of ways, we are happy to discuss alternative arrangements if the working pattern you are looking for is not specifically indicated.

We’re committed to continually building a safe and respectful workplace, where all our people feel appreciated and accepted. Through the creation of endorsed employee-led diversity networks which promote cultural, disability, LGBTI+, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and gender equality, we’re leading the way to shape an environment where everybody can thrive.

We are proud to have been recognised for our efforts in inspiring change and accelerating progress – check out our careers site for recent recognition in this space.

Next steps
If this sounds like the sort of role for you, apply now!

By applying to this job, you will be assessed against the Deloitte Global Talent Standards. We’ve designed these standards to provide our clients with a consistent and exceptional Deloitte employee experience globally.

At Deloitte, we know we’re at our best when we look out for one another; prioritise respect, fairness, development and wellbeing; foster an inclusive culture and embrace diversity in all forms. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment regardless of their background, experience, identity, ability or thinking style, and if you need assistance or an accommodation during the application process for accessibility reasons this is available upon request.

The preferred candidate will be subject to background screening by Deloitte or by their external third-party provider.

Description:
Job Requisition ID: 29908

Receive unparalleled professional development through our year-round graduate learning academy
Be prepared to be given trust, exposure and real responsibility from day one
Join an award-winning team!

Technology has revolutionised the business space and is now more powerful than ever. But with great power comes great responsibility. That’s why we’re here. Part risk, part tech, we help clients protect their intellectual property and data!

Who are we?
Call us biased, but we’re probably the people with the coolest jobs at Deloitte. We help clients navigate tech risks through internal investigations and forensically analysing electronic evidence collected from phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems. Then, we design solutions that help our clients risk-align and future-proof their systems. Pretty cool, right?

What will your typical day look like?
We’ll be honest, it’s hard to tell you what an average day will look like at Deloitte because every day is just so different! Working on projects with an impressive portfolio of top-tier clients, you’ll get enviable experience as you:

Get exposure to tracing data breaches, intellectual property theft, misuse of computer systems and fraudulent activity (such as corruption and money laundering)
Roll up your sleeves to investigate electronic evidence collected from mobile phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems
Design solutions for engagements relating to electronic discovery, forensic investigations, legal support and digital forensics
Explore and identify patterns in data to underpin decisions and outcomes for clients
Track evidence and prepare detailed reports on forensic analysis findings

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.
We know that as a student, you may not necessarily have a ton of work experience, and that’s okay! At Deloitte, we value your potential to grow more than anything else.


Is studying a degree in Computer Science, IT, Software Engineering, Digital Forensics, Data Science or InfoSys
Is comfortable with turning ambiguous problems and open-ended tasks into creative solutions
Is passionate about investigating data to uncover hidden insights
Has a keen eye for detail and possesses strong communication and writing skills
Works best collaboratively – you thrive when working in a team!
Demonstrates a high level of integrity and maintains confidentiality at all times (this is integral considering the nature of work we do!)

Why Deloitte?
At Deloitte, we create positively differentiated work experiences that enable our people to feel valued and achieve their full potential. Deloitte Australia opens the door to a career that can cross borders virtually and physically across Asia Pacific to gain experience and access projects beyond Australia’s borders. We value difference, and embrace people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. Knowing that people work best in a variety of ways, we are happy to discuss alternative arrangements if the working pattern you are looking for is not specifically indicated.

We’re committed to continually building a safe and respectful workplace, where all our people feel appreciated and accepted. Through the creation of endorsed employee-led diversity networks which promote cultural, disability, LGBTI+, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and gender equality, we’re leading the way to shape an environment where everybody can thrive.

We are proud to have been recognised for our efforts in inspiring change and accelerating progress – check out our careers site for recent recognition in this space.

Next steps
If this sounds like the sort of role for you, apply now!

By applying to this job, you will be assessed against the Deloitte Global Talent Standards. We’ve designed these standards to provide our clients with a consistent and exceptional Deloitte employee experience globally.

At Deloitte, we know we’re at our best when we look out for one another; prioritise respect, fairness, development and wellbeing; foster an inclusive culture and embrace diversity in all forms. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment regardless of their background, experience, identity, ability or thinking style, and if you need assistance or an accommodation during the application process for accessibility reasons this is available upon request.

The preferred candidate will be subject to background screening by Deloitte or by their external third-party provider.

Company Description

Interested in building and executing geospatial analytics on top of millions of square kilometres of aerial imagery working closely with key property insurance customers? Nearmap is recruiting for a mid-level Data Scientist to join the AI Output Systems team within the AI Systems group.

Company Description:
Nearmap is a Sydney-based global location intelligence company. We have tens of petabytes of high quality aerial imagery covering half a million square kilometres a year at 5-7cm resolution, and regularly captured imagery dating back to 2009. We produce automated 3D models of entire cities, and rich AI-driven vector maps, which turns our visual content into semantic information to power decisions in a wide range of organisations.

In the AI Output Systems team we design, build, and operate software systems that transform aerial imagery to insight. Our technology stack is based on the Python scientific libraries and traverses deep learning technology such as Tensorflow and Pytorch, cloud native technology such as Kubernetes, Kubeflow and Kafka, and computational geometry / GIS tools such as the Shapely and GeoPandas libraries.

Nearmap is a high-growth company, the ideal candidate will embrace an environment where things happen quickly and continuously. We aim for all employees to feel supported in their career development, with an abundance of opportunities for mentorship and cross-functional team projects.

It all started with an idea at Block in 2013. Initially built to take the pain out of peer-to-peer payments, Cash App has gone from a simple product with a single purpose to a dynamic app, bringing a better way to send, spend, invest, borrow and save to our millions of monthly active users. Our offices are great, but many of our roles can be done remotely from the countries where Block operates. We tailor our experience to champion our employees’ creativity and productivity wherever they are.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Be part of the Award Winning CIMIC Graduate Program
CIMIC Group invests in future leaders by providing graduates with exposure to a global organisation across multiple industries. The CIMIC Group graduate program gives graduates the opportunity to learn and develop whilst working on some of the worlds’ most iconic construction, mining, mineral processing, services, and public private partnership projects – you’ll be part of something BIGGER.
Graduates enter the program working at one of the CIMIC Group Operating Companies: CPB Contractors, Leighton Asia, Sedgman, UGL or EIC Activities. Over the course of the program rotations and industry exposure activities are also available at CIMIC and Pacific Partnerships.
Graduates receive structured, on-the-job training, guided learning plans and leadership mentoring. Over the two-year program, you will experience two one-year rotations with placements in various roles, projects or CIMIC Group companies and be building your career.

The data scientist is responsible for delivering data science and advanced analytics projects that contribute to audience selection and personalisation for customer recommendations, offers and 1-1 marketing campaigns, and improved health insurance business performance.
As well as bringing strong data processing and technical data science capabilities; you will also enjoy working closely with business stakeholders to understand requirements and translate these into data-driven approaches; bringing fresh ideas to ensure that data science projects are supporting the delivery of the health insurance business strategy and the customer analytics roadmap.

Execute analytical approaches, including (but not limited to) developing / training / optimising machine learning models, other forms of analytical modelling (e.g. descriptive, predictive) and applied statistics
Leverage capabilities of the new data science platform to productionise relevant analytical models / outputs

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Technology has revolutionised the business space and is now more powerful than ever. But with great power comes great responsibility. That’s why we’re here. Part risk, part tech, we help clients protect their intellectual property and data!

Who are we?
Call us biased, but we’re probably the people with the coolest jobs at Deloitte. We help clients navigate tech risks through internal investigations and forensically analysing electronic evidence collected from phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems. Then, we design solutions that help our clients risk-align and future-proof their systems. Pretty cool, right?

What will your typical day look like?
We’ll be honest, it’s hard to tell you what an average day will look like at Deloitte because every day is just so different! Working on projects with an impressive portfolio of top-tier clients, you’ll get enviable experience as you:

Get exposure to tracing data breaches, intellectual property theft, misuse of computer systems and fraudulent activity (such as corruption and money laundering)
Roll up your sleeves to investigate electronic evidence collected from mobile phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems
Design solutions for engagements relating to electronic discovery, forensic investigations, legal support and digital forensics
Explore and identify patterns in data to underpin decisions and outcomes for clients
Track evidence and prepare detailed reports on forensic analysis findings

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.
We know that as a student, you may not necessarily have a ton of work experience, and that’s okay! At Deloitte, we value your potential to grow more than anything else.


Is studying a degree in Computer Science, IT, Software Engineering, Digital Forensics, Data Science or InfoSys
Is comfortable with turning ambiguous problems and open-ended tasks into creative solutions
Is passionate about investigating data to uncover hidden insights
Has a keen eye for detail and possesses strong communication and writing skills
Works best collaboratively – you thrive when working in a team!
Demonstrates a high level of integrity and maintains confidentiality at all times (this is integral considering the nature of work we do!)

Why Deloitte?
At Deloitte, we create positively differentiated work experiences that enable our people to feel valued and achieve their full potential. Next steps
If this sounds like the sort of role for you, apply now!

By applying to this job, you will be assessed against the Deloitte Global Talent Standards. We’ve designed these standards to provide our clients with a consistent and exceptional Deloitte employee experience globally.

At Deloitte, we know we’re at our best when we look out for one another; prioritise respect, fairness, development and wellbeing; foster an inclusive culture and embrace diversity in all forms. Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

And then go and find all the ways to make that happen. At Deloitte Digital, we have all the people and tools to make those big ideas a reality in a way that no-one else can. You’ll find that working with people with backgrounds in fields from AI to creative technology, engineering to climate and sustainability, and scientists to futurists, makes for some pretty powerful inspiration to come up with those big ideas.

We are in the business of solving bigger problems with connected, creative solutions that have the ability to transform businesses.

The Creative practice is part of Deloitte Digital. We bring together a group of the world's most awarded creatives with the intellectual depth of the world's largest consulting firm. All underpinned by Deloitte’s deep industry and technical knowledge, the business provides Creative Consulting, Creative Agency of Record, Brand Transformation, Visual and Interactive Design, Invention and Behaviour Change services.

We work with a wide range of clients, from blue chip corporations to innovative start-ups, helping them adapt to and harness new media and technology. The culture of Deloitte Digital is one that celebrates difference, education, inclusivity and the relentless pursuit of excellence. We’d love to see what you can add.

Enough about us, let’s talk about you

This role requires an enthusiastic creatively-minded strategist, some experience in agency or industry (strategy/creative/digital etc) is advantageous, with a passion for creativity and ideas and the ability to present with confidence.

You will have a strong interest in and aptitude for business strategy, human behaviour and psychology.

You are analytical and strategically-minded with an awareness of market data and developments and the ability to interpret data into insights.

You are a problem-solver with ability to digest and condense complex information into clear, engaging briefs and supported recommendations.

We’re looking for someone who looks forwards not backwards. Who gets excited about collaborating with people with vastly different skillsets. Someone who feels comfortable with ambiguity, making decisions and be able to figure stuff out.

You have an academic mind, you may be a year into a research or marketing strategy position. You would have tertiary education / a masters in fields such as business, law, social sciences, psychology or similar.


Have great communication skills with the ability to present articulately and inspire others

Bring together inputs from multi skilled teams within Deloitte Digital and Deloitte Consultancy to gather inputs across functions and answer challenging problems


Understand your clients’ businesses and industries and seek to find value-adds - learn what questions to ask, have a can-do attitude and add value

Have awareness what’s going on across all live projects, look to anticipate issues and escalate them to managers


Develop the strategic direction for client businesses and projects, working alongside an Account Director / Strategist

Understand clients’ business and marketing objectives and translate those into the clear task to solve for each brief

Write succinct, insights-based briefs that inspire and inform creative teams to do their best work

Understand your clients’ commercial objectives and how we deliver on those through creative work


Be a champion for world class creative work

Take an interest and have awareness of new innovations in creativity to inform our work

Analyse how well the creative answers the brief and campaign objectives, and provide clear and honest feedback to help make the work better

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Immersive Technologies is one of the world's most successful companies in driving continuous improvement of human performance within the mining industry. We're part of the global Komatsu Group of companies, and are the world's largest supplier of mining equipment simulators, with our solutions deployed in over 50 different counties.
Our staff love Immersive because we have some of the most exciting and interesting development projects in Perth, and our products make a genuine difference in the safety and performance of operators. Our projects involve real-time simulation, low-level hardware interfacing, web development, and data management and analytics. Our developers get to work across our full and diverse technology stack, so there are plenty of chances to learn and develop new skills.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Be part of the Award Winning CIMIC Graduate Program
CIMIC Group invests in future leaders by providing graduates with exposure to a global organisation across multiple industries. The CIMIC Group graduate program gives graduates the opportunity to learn and develop whilst working on some of the worlds’ most iconic construction, mining, mineral processing, services, and public private partnership projects – you’ll be part of something BIGGER.
Graduates enter the program working at one of the CIMIC Group Operating Companies: CPB Contractors, Leighton Asia, Sedgman, UGL or EIC Activities. Over the course of the program rotations and industry exposure activities are also available at CIMIC and Pacific Partnerships.
Graduates receive structured, on-the-job training, guided learning plans and leadership mentoring. Over the two-year program, you will experience two one-year rotations with placements in various roles, projects or CIMIC Group companies and be building your career.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Description:
Are you curious about how digital is changing the world?
Join Accenture and help transform leading organizations and communities around the world. Autumn Compass is an algorithmic trading firm combining the disciplines of software engineering, data science and economic theory to develop highly automated and profitable trading strategies. We believe in quick experimentation, scientific reasoning and delving into the technical complexities of the systems we interact with to find our competitive advantage.
The role is based in Sydney CBD, but with very flexible working from home options.

Fun, fast paced and in IT you will have opportunity to work on multiple platforms and cutting-edge technologies. As family owned dynamic fresh food retailer who is rapidly growing, to thrive you will need to be open to being incredibly flexible and agile in order to meet business demands. In other words, it is busy and very fun!
As for our team, we are a small team of innovative developers who deliver quality solutions to the technical challenges of a rapidly growing company who have been a household name since 1971.
The Company
Harris Farm Markets has built a strong reputation for delivering good quality fresh food at great value for our customers.

Join us on our mission to make a better world of work.
Culture Amp revolutionizes how over 25 million employees across 5,000 companies create a better world of work. As the global platform leader for employee experience, Culture Amp empowers companies of all sizes and industries to transform employee engagement, develop high performing teams, and retain talent via cutting-edge research, powerful technology, and the largest employee dataset in the world. Culture Amp is backed by 10 years of innovation, leading capital venture funds, and offices in the U.S, U.K, Germany and Australia. Culture Amp is recognized as one of the world’s top private cloud companies by Forbes and one of the most innovative workplace companies by Fast Company.

Hi, we’re PEXA!
We know you’ll Google us before applying, so let’s keep this brief. PEXA revolutionised the way that property is settled in Australia, turning a paper-based process into a digital one. Our solution is a world-first, with over 500 people across Australia and an expanding international team, we’re helping 20,000+ families into their homes each week.
We’re passionate about solving problems for our customers – always striving to set the standard for how property is bought and sold. Being awarded as one of the best places to work in Australia is a recognition of our culture and commitment to innovation, customers and our community.
We’re growing fast, that is where you come in.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Technology has revolutionised the business space and is now more powerful than ever. But with great power comes great responsibility. That’s why we’re here. Part risk, part tech, we help clients protect their intellectual property and data!

Who are we?
Call us biased, but we’re probably the people with the coolest jobs at Deloitte. We help clients navigate tech risks through internal investigations and forensically analysing electronic evidence collected from phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems. Then, we design solutions that help our clients risk-align and future-proof their systems. Pretty cool, right?

What will your typical day look like?
We’ll be honest, it’s hard to tell you what an average day will look like at Deloitte because every day is just so different! Working on projects with an impressive portfolio of top-tier clients, you’ll get enviable experience as you:

Get exposure to tracing data breaches, intellectual property theft, misuse of computer systems and fraudulent activity (such as corruption and money laundering)
Roll up your sleeves to investigate electronic evidence collected from mobile phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems
Design solutions for engagements relating to electronic discovery, forensic investigations, legal support and digital forensics
Explore and identify patterns in data to underpin decisions and outcomes for clients
Track evidence and prepare detailed reports on forensic analysis findings

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. What we do
We provide easy, instant access to high-resolution aerial imagery, city-scale 3D content, AI datasets and integrated geospatial tools, with wide-scale coverage across the USA, Canada, Australia and New Zealand. At the core of it, we’re a location content company, a visual analytics company, and a software as a service company. Innovation is weaved into our DNA.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Graduates receive structured, on-the-job training, guided learning plans and leadership mentoring. Over the two-year program, you will experience two one-year rotations with placements in various roles, projects or CIMIC Group companies and be building your career.

Immersive Technologies is one of the world's most successful companies in driving continuous improvement of human performance within the mining industry. We're part of the global Komatsu Group of companies, and are the world's largest supplier of mining equipment simulators, with our solutions deployed in over 50 different counties.
Our staff love Immersive because we have some of the most exciting and interesting development projects in Perth, and our products make a genuine difference in the safety and performance of operators. Our projects involve real-time simulation, low-level hardware interfacing, web development, and data management and analytics. Our developers get to work across our full and diverse technology stack, so there are plenty of chances to learn and develop new skills.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

The data scientist is responsible for delivering data science and advanced analytics projects that contribute to audience selection and personalisation for customer recommendations, offers and 1-1 marketing campaigns, and improved health insurance business performance.
As well as bringing strong data processing and technical data science capabilities; you will also enjoy working closely with business stakeholders to understand requirements and translate these into data-driven approaches; bringing fresh ideas to ensure that data science projects are supporting the delivery of the health insurance business strategy and the customer analytics roadmap.
How will I help?
Execute analytical approaches, including (but not limited to) developing / training / optimising machine learning models, other forms of analytical modelling (e.g. descriptive, predictive) and applied statistics
Leverage capabilities of the new data science platform to productionise relevant analytical models / outputs

Fluent English verbal and written communication skills essential

We primarily seek to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of organisations at all stages of the data transformation journey from designing the change required, to delivering and managing that change and providing assurance around change initiatives.

Conduct gap analysis on client’s current business landscape (i.e. operating model, business processes) to identify and define key recommendations and opportunities to uplift business performance
Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment
Ability to structure, break down and solve complex problems through synthesis of information, quantitative thinking and analysis
Ability to interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially foucssed recommendations to inform business decisions
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, capable of working effectively with people at all levels in an organization
Strong sense of ownership of outcomes with the drive to self-start and take initiative
A passion for working collaboratively with diverse teams, and to create an including environment for everyone
Ability to structure and facilitate client stakeholder interviews

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Big data, information and analytics. Three words that spark apprehension in most businesses. What will your typical day look like?

As a Senior Consultant in our Data & AI team, focussing on Analytics & AI strategy, you will use your consulting skills to help clients make the right choices and take the right actions towards better use of Analytics and AI to achieve their business goals. As technical, strategy and industry experts, we understand clients’ challenges and define compelling strategies to meet their vision for becoming insight driven. A Senior Consultant will develop compelling interactions and presentations to showcases strategies, operating models and transformational business cases to clients across a range of industries, including Financial Services, Insurance, Government, Energy & Resources, Life Sciences & Healthcare, Telecommunications and Consumer Products.

Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Hi, we’re PEXA!
We know you’ll Google us before applying, so let’s keep this brief. PEXA revolutionised the way that property is settled in Australia, turning a paper-based process into a digital one. Our solution is a world-first, with over 500 people across Australia and an expanding international team, we’re helping 20,000+ families into their homes each week.
We’re passionate about solving problems for our customers – always striving to set the standard for how property is bought and sold. Being awarded as one of the best places to work in Australia is a recognition of our culture and commitment to innovation, customers and our community.
We’re growing fast, that is where you come in.
*
What it’s like to work here*

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.
