Call us biased, but we’re probably the people with the coolest jobs at Deloitte. We help clients navigate tech risks through internal investigations and forensically analysing electronic evidence collected from phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems. Then, we design solutions that help our clients risk-align and future-proof their systems. Pretty cool, right?

What will your typical day look like?
We’ll be honest, it’s hard to tell you what an average day will look like at Deloitte because every day is just so different! Working on projects with an impressive portfolio of top-tier clients, you’ll get enviable experience as you:

Get exposure to tracing data breaches, intellectual property theft, misuse of computer systems and fraudulent activity (such as corruption and money laundering)
Roll up your sleeves to investigate electronic evidence collected from mobile phones, computers, networks, storage devices and backup systems
Design solutions for engagements relating to electronic discovery, forensic investigations, legal support and digital forensics
Explore and identify patterns in data to underpin decisions and outcomes for clients
Track evidence and prepare detailed reports on forensic analysis findings

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.
We know that as a student, you may not necessarily have a ton of work experience, and that’s okay! At Deloitte, we value your potential to grow more than anything else.


Is studying a degree in Computer Science, IT, Software Engineering, Digital Forensics, Data Science or InfoSys
Is comfortable with turning ambiguous problems and open-ended tasks into creative solutions
Is passionate about investigating data to uncover hidden insights
Has a keen eye for detail and possesses strong communication and writing skills
Works best collaboratively – you thrive when working in a team!
Demonstrates a high level of integrity and maintains confidentiality at all times (this is integral considering the nature of work we do!)

Why Deloitte?
At Deloitte, we create positively differentiated work experiences that enable our people to feel valued and achieve their full potential. Deloitte Australia opens the door to a career that can cross borders virtually and physically across Asia Pacific to gain experience and access projects beyond Australia’s borders. We are proud to have been recognised for our efforts in inspiring change and accelerating progress – check out our careers site for recent recognition in this space.

Next steps
If this sounds like the sort of role for you, apply now!

By applying to this job, you will be assessed against the Deloitte Global Talent Standards. We’ve designed these standards to provide our clients with a consistent and exceptional Deloitte employee experience globally.

At Deloitte, we know we’re at our best when we look out for one another; prioritise respect, fairness, development and wellbeing; foster an inclusive culture and embrace diversity in all forms. Big data, information and analytics. Three words that spark apprehension in most businesses. Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment

Ability to interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially foucssed recommendations to inform business decisions

Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

What will your typical day look like?

Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment

Ability to interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially foucssed recommendations to inform business decisions

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

And then go and find all the ways to make that happen. At Deloitte Digital, we have all the people and tools to make those big ideas a reality in a way that no-one else can. You’ll find that working with people with backgrounds in fields from AI to creative technology, engineering to climate and sustainability, and scientists to futurists, makes for some pretty powerful inspiration to come up with those big ideas.

We are in the business of solving bigger problems with connected, creative solutions that have the ability to transform businesses.

The Creative practice is part of Deloitte Digital. We bring together a group of the world's most awarded creatives with the intellectual depth of the world's largest consulting firm. All underpinned by Deloitte’s deep industry and technical knowledge, the business provides Creative Consulting, Creative Agency of Record, Brand Transformation, Visual and Interactive Design, Invention and Behaviour Change services.

We work with a wide range of clients, from blue chip corporations to innovative start-ups, helping them adapt to and harness new media and technology. The culture of Deloitte Digital is one that celebrates difference, education, inclusivity and the relentless pursuit of excellence. We’d love to see what you can add.

Enough about us, let’s talk about you

This role requires an enthusiastic creatively-minded strategist, some experience in agency or industry (strategy/creative/digital etc) is advantageous, with a passion for creativity and ideas and the ability to present with confidence.

You will have a strong interest in and aptitude for business strategy, human behaviour and psychology.

You are analytical and strategically-minded with an awareness of market data and developments and the ability to interpret data into insights.

You are a problem-solver with ability to digest and condense complex information into clear, engaging briefs and supported recommendations.

We’re looking for someone who looks forwards not backwards. Who gets excited about collaborating with people with vastly different skillsets. Someone who feels comfortable with ambiguity, making decisions and be able to figure stuff out.

You have an academic mind, you may be a year into a research or marketing strategy position. You would have tertiary education / a masters in fields such as business, law, social sciences, psychology or similar.


Have great communication skills with the ability to present articulately and inspire others

Bring together inputs from multi skilled teams within Deloitte Digital and Deloitte Consultancy to gather inputs across functions and answer challenging problems


Understand your clients’ businesses and industries and seek to find value-adds - learn what questions to ask, have a can-do attitude and add value

Have awareness what’s going on across all live projects, look to anticipate issues and escalate them to managers


Develop the strategic direction for client businesses and projects, working alongside an Account Director / Strategist

Understand clients’ business and marketing objectives and translate those into the clear task to solve for each brief

Write succinct, insights-based briefs that inspire and inform creative teams to do their best work

Understand your clients’ commercial objectives and how we deliver on those through creative work


Be a champion for world class creative work

Take an interest and have awareness of new innovations in creativity to inform our work

Analyse how well the creative answers the brief and campaign objectives, and provide clear and honest feedback to help make the work better

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

About the team

Big data, information and analytics. Three words that spark apprehension in most businesses. But our team of experts are constantly curious and excited about combining our wonderful array of technological expertise to transform data into our clients’ most valuable assets, making their work smarter.

We primarily seek to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of organisations at all stages of the data transformation journey from designing the change required, to delivering and managing that change and providing assurance around change initiatives.

You will be an integral part of one of the fastest growing teams in Australia and build best in class data & AI solutions.

This role is for the AI & Automation team, which sits within the Data & AI, Strategy Analytics & Transformation in Deloitte Consulting.

What will your typical day look like?

As a Senior Consultant in our Data & AI team, focussing on Analytics & AI strategy, you will use your consulting skills to help clients make the right choices and take the right actions towards better use of Analytics and AI to achieve their business goals. As technical, strategy and industry experts, we understand clients’ challenges and define compelling strategies to meet their vision for becoming insight driven. A Senior Consultant will develop compelling interactions and presentations to showcases strategies, operating models and transformational business cases to clients across a range of industries, including Financial Services, Insurance, Government, Energy & Resources, Life Sciences & Healthcare, Telecommunications and Consumer Products.

Comprehend and learn about client’s current business state, competitors’ point(s) of differentiation, industry landscape to support the identification, evaluation and selection of solutions that most effectively support clients’ strategic and business objectives
Conduct gap analysis on client’s current business landscape (i.e. operating model, business processes) to identify and define key recommendations and opportunities to uplift business performance
Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment
Ability to structure, break down and solve complex problems through synthesis of information, quantitative thinking and analysis
Ability to interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially foucssed recommendations to inform business decisions
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, capable of working effectively with people at all levels in an organization
Strong sense of ownership of outcomes with the drive to self-start and take initiative
A passion for working collaboratively with diverse teams, and to create an including environment for everyone
Ability to structure and facilitate client stakeholder interviews

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.
We are a full-stack Australian-German quantum computing company, led and supported by the pioneers of diamond quantum information processing. Our HQs are in Canberra and Stuttgart, with additional locations across Australia and southern Germany. We are working with global technology leaders to develop quantum computing applications, integrate quantum with high-performance computing, solve materials science challenges and develop ultra-precise semiconductor manufacturing and control techniques. We are backed by leading venture-capital funds and major research and technology institutes.

Aurizon is seeking Graduates for our 2023 Graduate Campaign!
Our Graduates are permanent employees at Aurizon and this program provides an opportunity to develop technical and leadership capability across areas of our business. Our Company

At Nissan’s Global Customer Experience team (NCX) we design and develop world class experiences for car shoppers and owners. Based in Paddington London, at the Customer Experience Centre (CEC), you will be part of a talent packed & innovative organization with capabilities covering Strategy, Design, Analytics, Product, and Implementation that works closely with regional teams around the world to improve the ways customers can interact with Nissan.

In this role you will be joining CEDAR (Customer Experience Data, Analytics & Reporting) team within NCX to drive the value that can be derived from the data generated by millions of interactions each day across 145 markets from visitors to our digital channels and connected cars. For this we are looking for a hands-on Data Scientist with advanced machine learning skills combined with practical business acumen.


Your objective will be to examine trends to make intelligent data-driven decisions, find insights in data that others have not discovered, and run proof-of-concept exercises showing how predictions can be used to improve the customer experience.

Main tasks and responsibilities include;

Ability to work with multiple data sources and automate collection processes
Undertake preprocessing of structured and unstructured data
Analyze large amounts of information to discover trends and patterns
Build predictive models and machine-learning algorithms
Present information using data visualization techniques
Propose solutions and strategies to business challenges


Proven experience in Data Science / Advanced Analytics / Statistical Modelling
Proven experience in data wrangling, data cleansing, data mining
Good Understanding of supervised/unsupervised machine-learning algorithms, dimension reduction algorithms like PCA, auto-encoders
Experience with Tree based models – Decision Trees, Random Forest, Catboost etc. and Clustering techniques such as K-means, Agglomerative Clustering, DBSCAN
Ability to generate insights from data using EDA and exposure to ML model interpretability tools such as SHAP, LIME
Prior experience with NLP - Text Processing/Cleaning, Sentiment Analysis, Text Classification, Topic Modelling, feature extraction, transformers etc. Knowledge of NLTK, TF-IDF, GCP NLP API, BERT
Good working experience in programming using Python, SQL and data visualization libs like Matplotlib, Seaborn
Experience working with cloud platforms, GCP, version control using Git benficial
Ability to work with APIs for data extraction and experience in productionizing beneficial
Experience in using business intelligence tools like Power BI, Tableau
Problem-solving aptitude with great interpersonal and communication skills
Prior experience with customer analytics/ marketing data analytics in any industry will be plus
Fluent English verbal and written communication skills essential

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

About the team

Big data, information and analytics. Three words that spark apprehension in most businesses. But our team of experts are constantly curious and excited about combining our wonderful array of technological expertise to transform data into our clients’ most valuable assets, making their work smarter.

We primarily seek to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of organisations at all stages of the data transformation journey from designing the change required, to delivering and managing that change and providing assurance around change initiatives.

What will your typical day look like?

As technical, strategy and industry experts, we understand clients’ challenges and define compelling strategies to meet their vision for becoming insight driven. A Senior Consultant will develop compelling interactions and presentations to showcases strategies, operating models and transformational business cases to clients across a range of industries, including Financial Services, Insurance, Government, Energy & Resources, Life Sciences & Healthcare, Telecommunications and Consumer Products.

Provide advisory services to business leaders and align AI, analytics, automation or data solutions to clients’ needs and develop an objectives, strategies and approaches that help clients transform
Build solid foundations of a business case and key recommendations for implementing analytical solutions for the client in alignment with their business agenda and strategic drivers

Conduct gap analysis on client’s current business landscape (i.e. operating model, business processes) to identify and define key recommendations and opportunities to uplift business performance
Design and assist with implementation plans for approved recommendations. Managing the delivery and provisioning of
Apply knowledge of best practices and latest yet effective trends to design a strategic and business transformation plan that delivers on client’s strategic growth agenda and gain client’s buy-in to the transformation plan
Assist with implementing approved recommendations in transformation plan, including provision of procedure and supporting documentation
Plan and carry out assigned business analysis activities within engagement timeframes and budget, to ensure implemented solutions meet business requirements and enhance efficiencies

Enough about us, let’s talk about you.


Experience developing business unit or organizational level data or technology strategy within a consulting or industry environment
Ability to structure, break down and solve complex problems through synthesis of information, quantitative thinking and analysis
Ability to interpret analysis and modelling results in a business context and provide commercially foucssed recommendations to inform business decisions
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, capable of working effectively with people at all levels in an organization
Strong sense of ownership of outcomes with the drive to self-start and take initiative
A passion for working collaboratively with diverse teams, and to create an including environment for everyone
Ability to structure and facilitate client stakeholder interviews

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.

Quantum Brilliance is the world leader in room-temperature quantum computing using synthetic diamonds. Our unique vision is to make quantum computing available as an everyday technology, from data centres to remote and mobile systems like autonomous robots and satellites. In contrast to quantum computers that fill a room, we are developing quantum accelerators with more compute power than a classical supercomputer but a form-factor smaller than a lunchbox.

Our Company

Job Title: Junior Data Analyst - Western Public Health Unit
Job Description:
A unique opportunity exists to join the Western Public Health Unit in the role of Junior Data Analyst.
The Western Public Health Unit (WPHU) has been established to strengthen the public health response to infectious diseases and other health issues in the Western metropolitan region of Melbourne. The Unit is part of a system of three metropolitan Public Health Units; WPHU, North-eastern (NEPHU), South-eastern (SEPHU) and six regional Public Health Units to provide a new state-wide system of public health delivery and oversight. WPHU is currently responsible for COVID-related public health control activities and is taking on increasing responsibility for other communicable disease and health promotion activities, as part of the State’s overall public health response.
The Junior Data Analyst is a member of the Data, Epidemiology and Surveillance (DES) team. The role reports to the Lead Epidemiologist, will work closely with and under the direction of the Data Analyst, and will involve some supervision of activities undertaken by Data Assurance Officers.
